In article 47974sdcc12ucsdedu wsunjeevesucsdedu Fiberman writes
Is erythromycin effective in treating pneumonia

It depends on the cause of the pneumonia  For treating bacterial
pneumonia in young otherwisehealthy nonsmokers erythromycin
is usually considered the antibiotic of choice since it covers
the two mostcommon pathogens strep pneumoniae and mycoplasma
pneumoniae
 
